                    <Footer/>
                    <WebAddress>https://www.gpo.gov/docs/default-source/media-kit-files/how-a-bill-becomes-a-Law.pdf</WebAddress>
                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>Federal Lawmaking</Header>
                <Paragraph>An outline of the Federal lawmaking process—starting with the introduction of a bill by a Member of the Congress, continuing through its passage by both Chambers, and culminating in the President's approval—is available online in Portable Document Format (PDF).</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
